1
00:00:00,750 --> 00:00:03,374
Meet Dory 0.3.2.

2
00:00:04,850 --> 00:00:08,989
Your complete local Linux workspace,
built for Apple Silicon Macs.

3
00:00:09,850 --> 00:00:16,698
Start with one smaller Docker Core.
About 112 MB of duplicate compatibility payload—gone.

4
00:00:17,300 --> 00:00:23,529
Then add only what you need: Kubernetes, Linux Machines,
Debian, Ubuntu, or Kali desktops.

5
00:00:24,400 --> 00:00:33,211
Run and test graphical Linux applications beside your containers:
Retina-sharp windows, persistent disks, scoped Mac folders, and snapshots.

6
00:00:34,000 --> 00:00:37,947
For AI agents, launch a dedicated Preview sandbox VM.

7
00:00:38,300 --> 00:00:40,796
No host files are visible by default.

8
00:00:41,750 --> 00:00:43,627
Mount only what you choose.

9
00:00:44,250 --> 00:00:45,786
Set network to none.

10
00:00:46,350 --> 00:00:47,459
Roll back.

11
00:00:47,750 --> 00:00:50,374
Or let the temporary VM delete itself.

12
00:00:51,400 --> 00:00:55,901
Optional components are signed and removable.
Your workload data stays.

13
00:00:56,200 --> 00:00:59,912
Add custom domains. Add trusted HTTPS.

14
00:01:00,050 --> 00:01:04,658
Dory. Smaller core. Bigger possibilities.
Built for Mac. Open source.
